OUT OF THE DARKNESS COMES TREASURE:<br><br>
Damn Ed -- you are a poet.<br><br>
I killed kids too.  It was a miscalculated mortar round -- not my fault -- but what th hell does that mean -- I don't know.  I do know that I was a killer.  But what the fuck -- I know that  I could be callous and say the I CAME; I SAW; I KILLED; and I did a little shopping.  I know that sounds cold, and it's not true, but I want to say that I was not in a gunship doing what was necessary.<br><br>
I'm, like you, am not sure who I would be, if I was not a vet, but that's water over the bridge -- maybe a bridge too far for human nature that brings PTSD to our front door.  Soldiers, need to bellieve their cause and their deeds would help to bring about a better future -- boy were we suprised.-- or not  -- our identities were stripped -- as well as our sense of what it takes to be a human being.<br><br>
I'm getting to tied up with I'm trying to say -- maybe more next time.<br><br>
Paul<br>

